        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>{ Semper Occasio statim arripienda. Multa cadu[n]t inter Calicem,
                    supremaq[ue] Labra.</marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref person="Erasmus" book_title="Adagia"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <language ident="IT">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Chi ha Tempo, non aspetti Tempo.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="head" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Qui non est hodi&egrave;, cras min&ugrave;s aptus erit.</marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref person="Ovid" book_title="Remedia Amoris"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The opportunity must always be seized at once. 'Many things fall between the cup and the lip.' Whoever has time, do not await time [Don't put off until tomorrow
            what you can do today]. 'He who is not [ready] today, will be less ready tomorrow.'</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>Reru[m] omniu[m] preciosissima Pra[e]da,
                        occasio. Semper tibi pendeat hamus. Marius, nullis Repulsis excursus: Etiam Virescit Vulnere Virtus. <!--JG: Quote from the poet Aulus Furius Antias, whose writing only have survived when cited in other works (hence no use of the X-ref tag)-->.
                    Aliquo modo expugnat[u]r, quod undiq[ue] Inuaditur.</marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Gaius Marius"/> <!--JG: Not entirely sure-->
                    <X-ref person="Ovid" book_title="Ars amatoria"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Opportunity is the most valuable loot of all things. 'Have your hook always baited.'
            Marius,  running out without restraints: indeed, 'courage grows strong at a wound.' </translation> <!--JG: HIER GEBLEVEN!!-->
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
